ace%2C%20intended%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20the%20mosque%20had%20been%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EASI%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fasi-to-start-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-from-early-morning-friday-even-as-muslim-side-approaches-sc%5C%22%3Earrived%20at%20the%20site%20early%20on%20Friday%20morning%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20begin%20their%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20the%20masjid%20committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%20means%20that%20the%20ASI%20will%20continue%20examining%20the%20controversial%20religious%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20three-judge%20bench%20ordered%20the%20archaeological%20body%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20survey%20through%20%E2%80%9Cnon-invasive%E2%80%9D%20processes%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-allows-asi-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-without-excavation-or-damage-to-structure-using-non-invasive-process-234398%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20committee%20had%20planned%20to%20boycott%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20but%20journalist%20Omar%20Rashid%20tweeted%20on%20Friday%20afternoon%20that%20it%20has%20decided%20to%20cooperate%20with%20it%20in%20light%20of%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EJust%20in%3A%20After%20initially%20boycotting%20the%20ASI%20survey%20of%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%2C%20its%20caretakers%20now%2C%20following%20the%20SC%20upholding%20the%20survey%2C%20have%20decided%20to%20co-operate%20with%20ASI%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20party%20hopes%20the%20survey%20will%20be%20carried%20out%20in%20an%20impartial%20manner%2C%20without%20hurting%20the%20mosque%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fseemay%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40seemay%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Omar%20Rashid%20(%40omar7rashid)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fomar7rashid%2Fstatus%2F1687429304794370048%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%204%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresenting%20the%20committee%20in%20the%20top%20court%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Huzefa%20Ahmadi%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20%E2%80%93%20which%20prohibits%20altering%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20a%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20it%20existed%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20violated%20if%20the%20survey%20was%20conducted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20ordering%20the%20survey%2C%20and%20by%20going%20back%20in%20the%20history%20as%20to%20what%20happened%20500%20years%20ago%2C%20are%20you%20not%20violating%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%3F%E2%80%9D%20Ahmadi%20asked%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20you%20start%20a%20survey%2C%20you%20are%20unravelling%20the%20wounds%20of%20the%20past.%20And%20it%20is%20the%20very%20same%20thing%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20%5BAct%5D%20seeks%20to%20prohibit%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Justice%20Pardiwala%20told%20Ahmadi%20that%20if%20the%20suit%20stating%20that%20the%20mosque%20houses%20Hindu%20deities%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20prompted%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20to%20order%20the%20ASI%20survey%20%E2%80%93%20is%20not%20found%20to%20be%20maintainable%2C%20the%20results%20of%20the%20survey%20would%20not%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsider%20it%20from%20a%20different%20angle.%20Your%20principal%20argument%20is%20why%20undertake%20the%20survey%20when%20the%20suit%E2%80%99s%20maintainability%20is%20questioned.%20This%20survey%20is%20going%20to%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20report.%20Tomorrow%2C%20if%20you%20succeed%20in%20getting%20the%20plaint%20rejected%2C%20this%20survey%20will%20be%20nothing%20but%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20the%20survey%20take%20place%20because%20of%20the%20assurance%20given%20by%20Mr.%20Mehta%20that%20there%20is%20no%20invasive%20method.%20Let%20the%20report%20be%20given%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20also%20said%20that%20the%20mosque%20side%20will%20be%20able%20to%20challenge%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20findings%20if%20they%20wished%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20Mr.%20Ahmadi%2C%20this%20is%20an%20interlocutory%20order%20appointing%20a%20commissioner.%20Why%20should%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20interfere%3F%20We%20will%20keep%20open%20all%20issues%20regarding%20maintainability%2C%20objections%20to%20commission%20evidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CEven%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20case%2C%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20argument%20was%20made%20on%20the%20evidentiary%20value%20of%20ASI%20survey.%20These%20are%20issues%20to%20be%20addressed%20at%20the%20final%20hearing%20as%20to%20what%20is%20the%20evidentiary%20value%20of%20the%20survey.%20We%20will%20safeguard%20the%20structure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funderstanding-the-gyanvapi-mosque-dispute-what-does-the-places-of-worship-act-say%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Case%3A%20What%20Does%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Say%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20committee%20has%20also%20expressed%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20survey%20might%20damage%20parts%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20beginning%2C%20we%20have%20had%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20building%20may%20get%20damaged%20because%20it%20is%20an%20old%20structure.%20We%20claim%20it%20is%20600%20years%20old.%20The%20other%20side%20claims%20that%20it%20is%20even%20older%20%E2%80%93%201%2C000%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Farman%20Naqvi%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20committee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fasi-to-start-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-from-early-morning-friday-even-as-muslim-side-approaches-sc%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20building%20is%20not%20made%20from%20modern%20material%20or%20with%20modern%20technology.%20If%20a%20loose%20brick%20falls%20from%20somewhere%2C%20who%20will%20be%20responsible%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said%20that%20given%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20assurances%20that%20no%20damage%20would%20occur%2C%20it%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20stop%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20clarified%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20ASI%20by%20solicitor%20general%20of%20India%20Mr.%20Tushar%20Mehta%20that%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20the%20entire%20survey%20will%20be%20completed%20without%20any%20excavation%20at%20the%20site%20and%20without%20causing%20any%20destruction%20to%20the%20structure%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20order%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-allows-asi-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-without-excavation-or-damage-to-structure-using-non-invasive-process-234398%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20temple%20side%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Madhavi%20Divan%20also%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUltimately%2C%20it%20is%20the%20ASI.%20Its%20job%20is%20to%20preserve%20monuments%20%E2%80%A6%20so%20surely%20they%20cannot%20damage%20it.%20They%20know%20better.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%E2%80%99s%20order%20continued%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20order%20of%20the%20learned%20trial%20judge%20passed%20under%20Order%2026%20Rule%2010A%20of%20the%20CPC%20cannot%20be%20prima%20facie%20at%20this%20stage%2