01%2Fh8qg30rc_ratan-tata-throwback-ratan-tata-old-pic_625x300_23_January_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Falmost-got-married-ratan-tata-opens-up-about-falling-in-love-4269133%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20industrialist%20stated%20that%20the%20relationship%20fell%20apart%20after%20the%20India-China%20war%20started%20in%201962%20as%20his%20partner%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20visit%20India%20by%20her%20parents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Falmost-got-married-ratan-tata-opens-up-about-falling-in-love-4269133%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Falmost-got-married-ratan-tata-opens-up-about-falling-in-love-4269133%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Falmost-got-married-ratan-tata-opens-up-about-falling-in-love-4269133%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Interview%20%7C%20Fragile%20Democracies%2C%20the%20Global%20Shift%20Towards%20Right-Wing%20Populism%2C%20and%20Rising%20Inequality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F27172415%2FModi-crowd-pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPranab%20Bardhan%20is%20Professor%20Emeritus%20of%20Economics%20at%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley.%20Among%20the%20foremost%20global%20scholars%20of%20development%2C%20distribution%2C%20and%20trade%2C%20his%2012%20books%20and%20more%20than%20150%20journal%20articles%20cross%20disciplinary%20boundaries%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20critically%20grapple%20with%20the%20conditions%20needed%20for%20a%20more%20equitable%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3ELand%2C%20Labor%2C%20and%20Rural%20Poverty%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20considers%20the%20relationship%20between%20land%20tenure%2C%20agricultural%20employment%2C%20and%20rural%20poverty.%20The%20groundbreaking%20%3Cem%3EPolitical%20Economy%20of%20Development%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20integrated%20Marxian%20class%20analysis%20with%20a%20rational-choice%20methodology%20and%20a%20Weberian%20institutional%20lens%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20structural%20impediments%20that%20have%20slowed%20India%E2%80%99s%20industrial%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20new%20book%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hup.harvard.edu%2Fcatalog.php%3Fisbn%3D9780674259843%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EA%20World%20of%20Insecurity%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20re-examines%20the%20conditions%20underlying%20democratic%20disenchantment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20follows%2C%20King%E2%80%99s%20College%20lecturer%20in%20Comparative%20Political%20Economy%20Poornima%20Paidipaty%20interviews%20Bardhan%20on%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20global%20right%2C%20the%20nuances%20of%20decentralisation%2C%20and%20the%20role%20of%20the%20state%20in%20pursuing%20paths%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%20Paidipaty%3A%20%3Cem%3EA%20World%20of%20Insecurity%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Havard%2C%202022)%20covers%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20topics%2C%20from%20current%20economic%20inequality%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20populism%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20renewing%20institutions%20of%20social%20democracy%20across%20the%20globe.%20Maybe%20you%20can%20start%20by%20telling%20us%20about%20the%20inspiration%20behind%20the%20book%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20writer%2C%20what%20motivated%20you%20to%20piece%20all%20of%20this%20material%20together%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%20Bardhan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20a%20political%20economist%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20noticed%20that%20politics%20in%20many%20countries%20I%E2%80%99m%20interested%20in%2C%20both%20rich%20and%20poor%2C%20has%20been%20moving%20rightward%20(the%20major%20exception%20being%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20but%20even%20there%2C%20left-wing%20victories%20have%20been%20fragile).%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20understanding%20this%20global%20shift.%20Everyone%20talks%20about%20the%20rich%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Trump%2C%20Johnson%2C%20LePen%2C%20Meloni%2C%20the%20Sweden%20Democrats%2C%20among%20many%20others.%20Developing%20countries%20get%20less%20attention.%20In%20my%20study%2C%20I%20look%20at%20three%20developing%20countries%3A%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20and%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20202px)%2085vw%2C%20202px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04180253%2Fimage-1193-202x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22202%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04180253%2Fimage-1193-202x300.png%20202w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04180253%2Fimage-1193.png%20512w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666674%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20World%20of%20Insecurity%20by%20Pranab%20Bardhan%20(10%2F18%2F2022)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExisting%20work%20on%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20right%20revolves%20around%20the%20question%20of%20inequality%20%E2%80%93%20even%20in%20countries%20where%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20rising%2C%20it%20is%20already%20very%20high.%20But%20again%2C%20much%20of%20this%20work%20is%20focused%20on%20Western%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%2C%20and%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20broadening%20this%20scope.%20Despite%20having%20worked%20quite%20a%20lot%20on%20inequality%20as%20an%20economist%2C%20I%20had%20a%20sense%20that%20this%20was%20not%20the%20full%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20I%20felt%20that%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20an%20essential%20question%3A%20Why%20are%20working%20people%20rallying%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20multi-millionaires%3F%20This%20is%20particularly%20confounding%20given%20that%20these%20billionaires%2C%20once%20they%20come%20to%20power%2C%20almost%20inevitably%20reduce%20taxes%20on%20the%20rich%20and%20weaken%20restrictions%20on%20the%20financial%20and%20corporate%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20motivation%20for%20writing%20the%20book%20is%20that%20existing%20discussions%20tend%20to%20exclude%20any%20reflection%20on%20the%20Chinese%20model%20as%20an%20alternative.%20I%20discuss%20the%20advantages%20of%20the%20Chinese%20model%20of%20economic%20development%2C%20but%20also%20emphasise%20that%20many%20of%20the%20ugly%20features%20of%20Chinese%20development%20are%20the%20result%20of%20the%20underlying%20authoritarianism.%20After%20a%20lengthy%20discussion%20of%20these%20benefits%20and%20downsides%2C%20I%20suggest%20that%20authoritarianism%20is%20neither%20necessary%20nor%20sufficient%20for%20promoting%20the%20beneficial%20aspects%20of%20Chinese%20policymaking%20and%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20I%20took%20the%20book%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20reflect%20on%20what%20comes%20next%20%E2%80%93%20what%20do%20we%20do%20about%20this%20global%20trend%3F%20I%20devote%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20book%20to%20this%20question%2C%20trying%20to%20conceptualise%20what%20I%20call%20the%20rejuvenation%20of%20social%20democracy.%20How%20do%20we%20cultivate%20new%20thinking%20about%20social%20democratic%20transformations%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20In%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20many%20scholars%20have%20highlighted%20the%20impact%20of%20rising%20economic%20inequality%20on%20political%20polarisation%20and%20social%20stratification.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20that%20distinguishes%20your%20book%20is%20the%20distinction%20you%20draw%20between%20inequality%20and%20insecurity.%20Can%20you%20talk%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20those%20terms%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20argue%20for%20a%20shift%20in%20emphasis%20from%20inequality%20to%20insecurity.%20I%20question%20the%20explanatory%20value%20of%20inequality%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20workers%20are%20far%20more%20concerned%20with%20their%20living%20standards%20relative%20to%20others%20in%20their%20community%20than%20they%20are%20with%20the%20top%201%25.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20or%20care%20about%20the%20lifestyle%20of%20the%20global%20elite.%20However%2C%20workers%20%3Cem%3Eare%3C%2Fem%3E%20acutely%20aware%20of%20the%20sources%20of%20insecurity%20in%20their%20life.%20Among%20these%2C%20economic%20insecurity%20is%20obvious%3A%20job%20loss%2C%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20in%20rich%20countries%2C%20since%20China%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20the%20WTO%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20book%2C%20I%20also%20discuss%20other%20sources%20of%20insecurity.%20One%20of%20these%20I%20call%20cultural%20insecurity.%20Culture%20is%20an%20ambiguous%20term%2C%20but%20this%20sort%20of%20insecurity%20takes%20specific%20forms%20%E2%80%93%20in%20rich%20countries%2C%20it%20often%20manifests%20as%20fears%20over%20immigration.%20In%20my%20view%2C%20the%20economic%20side%20of%20these%20fears%20are%20not%20really%20what%20is%20at%20play%2C%20especially%20since%20immigration%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20proven%20to%20bring%20net%20economic%20benefits.%20The%20fears%20are%2C%20I%20think%2C%20primarily%20about%20threats%20to%20a%20perceived%20%E2%80%9Ctraditional%E2%80%9D%20form%20of%20life.%20The%20role%20of%20perception%20is%20important%20here%3B%20firstly%2C%20because%20second%20and%20third%20generation%20immigrants%20tend%20to%20assimilate%20into%20local%20traditions%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20because%20surveys%20have%20found%20that%20people%20tend%20to%20grossly%20overestimate%20numbers.%20They%20have%20an%20exaggerated%20perception%20of%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20countries%20tend%20to%20attract%20far%20less%20immigration%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20the%20cultural%20issue%20often%20takes%20a%20different%20form%20%E2%80%93%20religious%20majoritarianism%20or%20ethnic%20nationalism.%20This%20is%20the%20case%20in%20both%20Turkey%20and%20India%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Poland%20and%20Hungary.%20These%20movements%20are%20tied%20together%20by%20what%20I%20refer%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmanufactured%20victimhood%E2%80%9D%3A%20when%20the%20majority%20population%20somehow%20has%20a%20contrived%20fear%20of%20victimisation%20by%20a%20minority.%20This%20is%20often%20the%20result%20of%20historical%20resentment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20India%20there%20is%20resentment%20among%20Hindus%20that%20Muslims%20ruled%20600%20years%20ago.%20During%20the%20Bosnian%20War%20of%20the%201990s%2C%20I%20remember%20seeing%20a%20cartoon%20in%20which%20a%20Bosnian%20Serb%20and%20a%20Bosnian%20Muslim%20were%20stabbing%20each%20other%2C%20with%20one%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20for%201432%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20other%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20is%20for%201521.%E2%80%9D%20This%20stoking%20of%20historical%20memory%20is%20something%20right-wing%20demagogues%20are%20very%20good%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fchristophe-jaffrelot-rss-narendra-modi%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Not%20Hindu%20Nationalism%2C%20but%20Society%20That%20Has%20Changed%E2%80%99%3A%20Christophe%20Jaffrelot%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3A%20I%20share%20your%20scepticism%20regarding%20the%20explanatory%20power%20of%20rising%20inequality%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20explaining%20the%20global%20shift%20towards%20right-wing%20populism.%20On%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20much%20of%20this%20right-wing%20support%20is%20not%20coming%20from%20those%20people%20hardest%20hit%20by%20unequal%20economic%20distribution.%20For%20instance%2C%20Modi%20supporters%20in%20India%20often%20come%20from%20groups%20that%20have%20seen%20quite%20a%20few%20economic%20benefits%20in%20the%20recent%20years%20and%20whose%20prospects%20have%20not%20shrunk%20in%20absolute%20terms.%20Many%20of%20them%20are%20part%20of%20the%20rising%20lower%20middle%20classes.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fact%20that%20insecurity%20is%20a%20question%20of%20perception%20is%20also%20a%20great%20point.%20But%20just%20as%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20direct%20correspondence%20between%20economic%20deprivation%20and%20support%20for%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20the%20people%20who%20feel%20insecure%20over%20rising%20numbers%20of%20migrants%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20often%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20fewer%20immigrants%20(relative%20to%20large%20metropolitan%20areas).%20What%20is%20the%20relationship%20between%20this%20perception%20of%20insecurity%20and%20our%20changing%20global%20political%20economy%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20There%20is%2C%20as%20you%20say%2C%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20the%20support%20base%20for%20these%20parties%20between%20rich%20economies%20and%20poorer%20ones.%20In%20the%20US%20and%20Western%20Europe%2C%20the%20right%20is%20popular%20among%20older%2C%20rural%2C%20less%20educated%20voters.%20By%20contrast%2C%20much%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20support%20comes%20from%20the%20aspiring%20urban%20youth.%20Major%20metropolitan%20areas%20like%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20and%20Bangalore%20voted%20for%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20this%20is%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20cities%20like%20New%20York%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20and%20Chicago.%20These%20rising%20groups%20are%20mobilised%20by%20resentment%20for%20what%20they%20perceive%20to%20be%20a%20Western%20liberal%20elite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20talk%20us%20through%20some%20of%20the%20emerging%20alternatives%20to%20liberal%20capitalism%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20tensions%20that%20we%20see%20emerging%20very%20clearly%20now%20is%20that%20between%20the%20local%20and%20the%20federal%20or%20international.%20Political%20mobilisation%20around%20this%20issue%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20fall%20neatly%20onto%20our%20inherited%20political%20axes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20notion%20of%20community%20is%20often%20leveraged%20by%20the%20left.%20%5BHowever%5D%2C%20equally%2C%20one%20of%20Brexit%E2%80%99s%20key%20slogans%20is%20%E2%80%9Cback%20to%20the%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20i.e.%20back%20to%20the%20local%20community%20and%20away%20from%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20to%20be%20said%20for%20communitarian%20ideas%2C%20given%20that%20big%20bureaucracies%20often%20trample%20upon%20local%20initiatives%20and%20local%20ingenuity.%20Much%20of%20my%20work%20has%20been%20focused%20on%20structuring%20decentralisation%20in%20India.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20written%20theoretical%20papers%20and%20also%20collected%20data%20on%20village%20surveys%20carried%20out%2C%20especially%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20But%20having%20grown%20up%20in%20India%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20how%20oppressive%20local%20communities%20can%20be.%20We%20should%20not%20have%20an%20idealised%20notion%20of%20how%20a%20small%20village%20operates%20with%20respect%20to%20caste%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20debate%20dates%20back%20to%20decades%3B%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20key%20differences%20between%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20one%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20Gandhi%20mobilised%20around%20the%20notion%20of%20the%20village%20republic%2C%20while%20Ambedkar%20described%20the%20Indian%20village%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sink%20of%20localism%2C%20a%20den%20of%20ignorance%2C%20narrow-mindedness%2C%20and%20communalism%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20constitutional%20debates%20of%201948.%20We%20are%20all%20familiar%20with%20the%20issues%20that%20arise%20from%20insiders%20seizing%20local%20political%20space%20%E2%80%93%20zoning%20restrictions%2C%20professional%20licensing%2C%20school%20financing%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Decentralisation%2C%20thus%2C%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20worsen%20and%20entrench%20local%20inequalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20intervention%20can%20help%20catalyse%20changes%20of%20oppressive%20practices%20within%20communities.%20It%20can%20also%20help%20smooth%20out%20intra-community%20inequalities.%20In%20earlier%20research%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20examined%20how%20land%20distribution%20impacts%20political%20cooperation.%20Small%20communities%20are%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20in%20dealing%20with%20natural%20disasters%2C%20market%20mishaps%2C%20infrastructure%20investments%2C%20and%20the%20like.%20But%20there%20are%20also%20things%20local%20governments%20do%20very%20well%3B%20I%20try%20to%20find%20the%20balance%20between%20the%20two%20in%20my%20chapter%20on%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20This%20ties%20back%20to%20your%20argument%20about%20state%20capacity.%20There%20is%20an%20emerging%20dialogue%20in%20India%20regarding%20the%20importance%20of%20federalist%20structures%2C%20with%20some%20scholars%20and%20activists%20arguing%20for%20more%20decentralisation%20of%20power.%20This%20strand%20of%20thinking%20argues%20that%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20(through%20their%20brand%20of%20populism)%20are%20not%20turning%20away%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20foundations%3B%20instead%20they%20are%20building%20upon%20the%20historical%20institutions%20of%20a%20Nehruvian%20state%2C%20which%20used%20centralised%20power%20in%20order%20to%20expand%20state%20capacity.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20solution%20to%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20according%20to%20this%20view%2C%20is%20more%20decentralisation%20and%20less%20power%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20central%20government.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20conversation%20is%20gaining%20ground%20in%20light%20of%20the%20southern%20states%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Funderstanding-bjp-mukt-karnataka-from-the-north-south-perspective%5C%22%3Erejection%20of%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20elections.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20the%20reverse%3A%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20protector%20of%20civil%20liberties%20while%20states%20are%20seen%20as%20sites%20for%20the%20erosion%20of%20those%20liberties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20In%20the%20book%2C%20I%20argue%20that%20one%20advantage%20of%20the%20Chinese%20model%20is%20its%20unique%20blend%20of%20political%20centralisation%20combined%20with%20economic%20and%20administrative%20decentralisation.%20India%20exemplifies%20just%20the%20opposite%3A%20a%20decentralised%20political%20system%20with%20strong%20regional%20power%20groupings%2C%20combined%20with%20economic%20centralisation%20whereby%20regions%20depend%20on%20finance%20from%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20this%20discussion%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20writing%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Ambedkar%20advocated%20for%20more%20central%20power%20in%20order%20to%20combat%20the%20oppression%20of%20lower%20castes%2C%20like%20his%20Mahar%20community%2C%20a%20Dalit%20group%20in%20Maharashtra.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20he%20advocated%20a%20partial%20centralisation.%20Nehru%20was%20also%20concerned%20with%20keeping%20the%20country%20together%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Partition.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20these%20two%20elements%2C%20I%20think%20they%20gave%20the%20central%20government%20an%20unfair%20amount%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F10123319%2F670395.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22899%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F10123319%2F670395.jpeg%20700w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F10123319%2F670395-300x214.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-591539%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22641%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMembers%20of%20Dalit%20community%20display%20a%20portrait%20of%20BR%20Ambedkar%20during%20a%20%E2%80%98Bharat%20Bandh%E2%80%99%20over%20the%20%E2%80%98dilution%E2%80%99%20of%20SC%2F%20ST%20act.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFew%20governments%20can%20do%20what%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20done%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20if%20we%20think%2C%20for%20example%2C%20of%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20the%20communist%20control%20of%20Kerala%20in%201959.%20As%20per%20the%20advice%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20was%20president%20of%20the%20Congress%20Party%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Nehru%20imposed%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20in%20Kerala%2C%20whereby%20the%20central%20government%20dismissed%20the%20elected%20state%20government.%20That%E2%80%99s%20an%20example%20of%20a%20central%20government%20openly%20violating%20the%20wishes%20of%20an%20electorate.%20This%20has%20been%20repeated%20in%20several%20states%20over%20the%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20happened%20in%20an%20even%20more%20extreme%20form%20recently%2C%20with%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Without%20consulting%20the%20population%2C%20the%20state%20was%20broken%20into%20three%20centrally%20administered%20territories.%20Can%20you%20imagine%20if%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20the%20US%20broke%20up%20California%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20inconceivable.%20American%20federalism%20gives%20more%20power%20to%20local%20states.%20In%20the%201940s%2C%20when%20they%20considered%20what%20form%20an%20independent%20India%20should%20take%2C%20one%20idea%20put%20forward%20was%20that%20of%20a%20Confederation.%20This%20was%20proposed%20in%20order%20to%20stop%20Partition%2C%20but%20the%20notion%20was%20eventually%20dropped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20China%2C%20provincial%20and%20sub-provincial%20governments%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20power.%20This%20also%20means%20that%20they%20have%20a%20far%20better%20system%20for%20managing%20infrastructure%20financing%20and%20construction%20at%20the%20local%20level.%20Urban%20infrastructure%20is%20governed%20by%20companies%20organised%20by%20the%20city%20government.%20Out%20of%20the%20total%20government%20expenditure%20for%20the%20whole%20country%2C%20the%20amount%20that%20is%20spent%20at%20the%20sub-provincial%20level%2C%20not%20even%20at%20the%20state%20provincial%20level%2C%20is%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20total%20government%20expenditure.%20In%20India%2C%20it%20is%20about%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20municipal%20governments%20lack%20taxation%20power%20and%20are%20therefore%20financially%20strapped.%20Much%20of%20social%20expenditure%20takes%20place%20at%20the%20level%20of%20states%2C%20but%20money%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20central%20government.%20I%20refer%20to%20this%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20vertical%20fiscal%20imbalance%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20weak%20performance%20of%20local%20bodies%20in%20India%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20services%20and%20facilities%20is%20in%20part%20tied%20to%20it.%20By%20contrast%2C%20Chinese%20local%20governments%20are%20active%20in%20business%20development%20and%20not%20just%20in%20service%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-the-karnataka-election-results-are-a-big-jolt-for-the-bjp%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Karnataka%20Election%20Results%20Are%20a%20Big%20Jolt%20for%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3A%20Let%E2%80%99s%20turn%20to%20some%20of%20the%20solutions%20that%20the%20book%20puts%20forward.%20Your%20re-commitment%20to%20social%20democracy%20seems%20to%20resist%20widespread%20proclamations%20about%20the%20failure%20of%20democratic%20institutions.%20What%20exactly%20do%20you%20have%20in%20mind%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20My%20main%20focus%20is%20on%20universal%20basic%20income%20(UBI)%20and%20job%20creation.%20For%20developing%20countries%2C%20with%20fairly%20weak%20social%20safety%20nets%2C%20UBI%20can%20be%20very%20effective%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20mitigating%20gender%20disparities.%20In%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20the%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20women%20are%20not%20earning%20any%20income%2C%20despite%20performing%20back-breaking%20domestic%20work.%20But%20roughly%2080%25%20of%20Indians%20have%20a%20bank%20account%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20government%20transfer%20would%20hugely%20empower%20women%20who%20currently%20depend%20on%20their%20partners%20for%20survival.%20UBI%20becomes%20very%20appealing%20from%20the%20starting%20point%20of%20insecurity%3A%20offering%20an%20exit%20option%20for%20those%20who%20have%20been%20forced%20into%20work%20like%20manual%20scavenging%20for%20centuries%20due%20to%20their%20caste.%20Minimising%20sources%20of%20insecurity%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20a%20more%20powerful%20justification%20than%20that%20of%20anti-poverty%20%E2%80%93%20it%20avoids%20the%20discussion%20of%20substituting%20income%20transfers%20for%20other%20social%20safety%20programmes%20which%20may%20in%20fact%20be%20more%20effective%20at%20reducing%20poverty%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20also%20suggest%20that%20UBI%20can%20be%20effective%20at%20strengthening%20labour%20movements%20by%20unifying%20the%20interests%20of%20informal%20and%20formal%2C%20unionised%20and%20non-unionised%2C%20service%20and%20manufacturing%20workers.%20In%20India%2C%20as%20in%20many%20developing%20countries%2C%20we%20see%20a%20small%20island%20of%20unionised%20workers%20surrounded%20by%20a%20vast%20ocean%20of%20informal%20workers.%20That%20small%20group%20gets%20access%20to%20benefits%20like%20pensions%20which%20the%20others%20do%20not%20have.%20Policies%20like%20UBI%2C%20which%20benefit%20both%20formal%20and%20informal%20workers%2C%20help%20bridge%20this%20gulf%2C%20softening%20labour%20market%20divisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20also%20stress%20upon%20the%20importance%20of%20wage%20subsidies%20for%20the%20employment%20of%20young%20people%2C%20who%20are%20largely%20unemployed%20or%20underemployed%20in%20much%20of%20the%20developing%20world.%20And%20I%20reiterate%20the%20power%20of%20job%20creation%20via%20the%20green%20energy%20transition%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20importance%20of%20giving%20the%20labour%20a%20voice%20in%20corporate%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnouriel-roubini-oligopoly-crony-capitalism%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Oligopoly%20in%20Corporate%20Sector%20Preventing%20India%E2%80%99s%20Growth%20From%20Going%20Higher%E2%80%99%3A%20Nouriel%20Roubini%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoornima%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EMaybe%20we%20can%20end%20by%20considering%20a%20few%20questions%20which%20are%20related%20to%20the%20issues%20you%20take%20on%20but%20are%20outside%20the%20direct%20scope%20of%20your%20book.%20You%20mention%20Branko%20Milanovi%C4%87%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3ECapitalism%20Alone%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2019)%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20argues%20that%20whatever%20criticisms%20we%20may%20have%20of%20capitalism%2C%20it%20has%20been%20responsible%20for%20transformative%20economic%20mobility%20over%20the%20past%20two%20centuries.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20defence%20of%20capitalism%20presents%20crucial%20questions%20regarding%20sustainability%3A%20both%20ecological%20sustainability%20and%20distributional%20sustainability.%20For%20example%2C%20Milanovi%C4%87%20focuses%20on%20the%20period%20since%20the%201970s%2C%20when%20low%20inflation%20enabled%20large-scale%2C%20debt-financed%20consumption%2C%20and%20subsequently%20a%20manufacturing%20boom%2C%20which%20raised%20commodity%20prices%20in%20places%20like%20Sub-Saharan%20Africa.%20This%20is%20more%20equitable%20than%20what%20we%20had%20before%2C%20but%20is%20it%20sustainable%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EPranab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20challenge%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20to%20harness%20technological%20innovation%20towards%20social%20ends.%20We%20ought%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20advances%20we%20make%20prioritise%20the%20interests%20of%20workers%20and%20give%20them%20a%20voice%20in%20decision-making.%20Democratising%20the%20decision-making%20structures%20in%20large%20corporations%20can%20allow%20us%20to%20determine%20the%20rate%20and%20pattern%20of%20innovations%20more%20collectively.%20We%20also%20need%20to%20democratise%20our%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20democracies%20in%20the%20world%20(both%20India%20and%20the%20US)%20have%20elections%20funded%20by%20private%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20anonymous%20electoral%20bond%20system%2C%20businessmen%20and%20companies%20are%20able%20to%20secure%20party%20favours.%20If%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20reform%20our%20politics%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20public%2C%20we%20ought%20to%20look%20at%20the%20sort%20of%20public%20funding%20models%20used%20by%20Belgium%2C%20Spain%2C%20Germany%2C%20Sweden%2C%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.phenomenalworld.org%2Finterviews%2Fpranab-bardhan%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cspan%20data-sheets-userformat%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3B2%26quot%3B%3A12801%2C%26quot%3B3%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%3A0%7D%2C%26quot%3B12%26quot%3B%3A0%2C%26quot%3B15%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BArial%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3B16%26quot%3B%3A10%7D%5C%22%20data-sheets-value%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%3A2%2C%26quot%3B2%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BPhenomenal%20World%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%