p%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20G20%20Health%20Agenda%20Undermines%20Its%20Credibility%20Among%20Traditional%20Allies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04141303%2FFjHNMmeakAEkbxa.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20G20%20priorities%20will%20be%20shaped%20in%20consultation%20with%20not%20just%20our%20G20%20partners%2C%20but%20also%20our%20fellow-travellers%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Union%20health%20minister%20Dr%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya.%20Addressing%20the%20Health%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20during%20the%20Voice%20of%20Global%20South%20Summit%20organised%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20in%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Mandaviya%20apparently%20chanted%20what%20Prime%20Minister%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1891014%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENarendra%20Modi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20already%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20to%20focus%20on%20long-term%20measures%20to%20build%20stronger%2C%20more%20resilient%20health%20systems%20that%20can%20prevent%2C%20prepare%20for%2C%20and%20respond%20to%20future%20health-related%20challenges%2C%20while%20maintaining%20essential%20health%20services.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20primary%20goal%20of%20the%C2%A0summit%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Censure%20that%20valuable%20inputs%20generated%20from%20partner%20countries%20in%20the%20Voice%20of%20Global%20South%20Summit%20deliberations%20receive%20due%20cognisance%20globally.%20India%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20presidency%20of%20the%20G20%20provides%20India%20a%20special%20and%20strong%20opportunity%20to%20channelise%20these%20inputs%20into%20the%20deliberation%20and%20discourse%20of%20the%20G20.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDisturbingly%2C%20as%20the%20days%20progress%20towards%20the%20Health%20Working%20Group%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Gandhi%20Nagar%20on%2017-18%20August%2C%20it%20has%20become%20clear%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20health%20agenda%20in%20the%20G20%20is%20likely%20to%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20developed%20countries%20and%20philanthropic%20foundations%20such%20as%20the%20Bill%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%20(BMGF)%2C%20say%20representatives%20of%20several%20developing%20countries%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%C2%A0has%20set%C2%A0three%20health%20priorities%20as%20part%C2%A0of%20its%C2%A0G-20%20presidency.%20First%2C%20health%20emergency%20prevention%2C%20preparedness%20and%20response%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20antimicrobial%20resistance%20(AMR)%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Fquestions-and-answers%2Fitem%2Fone-health%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20Health%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20framework.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%2C%20strengthening%20cooperation%20in%20the%20pharmaceutical%20sector%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20access%20and%20availability%20to%20safe%2C%20effective%2C%20quality%20and%20affordable%20medical%20countermeasures%20(vaccines%2C%20therapeutics%20and%20diagnostics).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20third%2C%20digital%20health%20innovations%20and%20solutions%20to%20aid%20universal%20health%20coverage%20and%20improve%20healthcare%20service%20delivery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20two%20priorities%C2%A0allegedly%C2%A0serve%20the%20purposes%20of%20the%20developed%20countries.%20On%20the%20third%20priority%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%20has%20apparently%20pushed%20back%20India%E2%80%99s%C2%A0request%C2%A0to%20make%20digital%20health%20tools%20a%20%E2%80%9CDigital%20Public%20Good%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHealth%20emergency%20prevention%2C%20preparedness%20and%20response%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20thrust%20of%20this%20priority%20is%20health%20and%20extending%20the%20idea%20of%20health%20emergency%20to%20AMR.%20%E2%80%9COne%20Health%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20jargon%20to%20describe%20that%20human%20health%20depends%20on%20the%20health%20of%20plants%2C%20animals%20and%20the%20environment.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20surveil%20pathogens%20causing%20infection%20among%20plants%20and%20animals%20to%20identify%20those%20of%20human%20pandemic%20potential%20and%20thus%20prevent%20the%20next%20pandemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20surveillance%20also%20requires%20collecting%20pathogen%20samples%20from%20plants%20and%20animals%20along%20with%20human%20pathogens%20and%20sharing%20them%20with%20the%20developed%20countries.%20This%20is%20very%20clear%20from%20the%20WHO%20Bureau%E2%80%99s%20text%20of%20a%20pandemic%20instrument%20that%20proposes%20that%20countries%20%E2%80%9Cimplement%20One%20Health%20surveillance%20mechanisms%20using%20data%20collected%20from%20and%20shared%20across%20human%2C%20animal%2C%20and%20environmental%20sources%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20preventing%20and%20controlling%20the%20spillover%20of%20pathogens%20with%20pandemic%20potential%20between%20humans%20and%20animal%20populations%2C%20as%20well%20as%20between%20different%20animal%20species%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20sharing%20of%20samples%20or%20their%20genetic%20sequences%20fully%20compromises%20the%20access%20and%20benefit-%20sharing%20provisions%C2%A0under%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2046%2F1%2F200318.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%C2%A0Biological%20Diversity%20Act%202002%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fobservances%2Fbiological-diversity-day%2Fconvention%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Convention%2520on%2520Biological%2520Diversity%2Cbeen%2520ratified%2520by%2520196%2520nations.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUN%20Convention%20on%C2%A0Biological%20Diversity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(CBD).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20CBD%2C%20any%20research%20benefits%20emerging%20out%20of%20any%20genetic%20materials%20including%20pathogens%C2%A0should%20be%C2%A0shared%20with%20the%20respective%20country%20of%20origin.India%E2%80%99s%C2%A0Biological%20Diversity%20Act%202002%20implements%20the%20access%20and%20benefit-sharing%20provisions%20at%20the%20national%20level.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fmodi-g20-india-paris-agreement-fact-check%5C%22%3EModi%20Says%20India%20Only%20G20%20Country%20to%20Fulfil%20Paris%20Agreement%20Obligations%20%E2%80%93%20But%20Tracker%20Says%20Otherwise%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20One%20Health%20agenda%20demands%20the%20transfer%20of%20genetic%20materials%20from%20the%20South%20to%20the%20North%20without%20any%20legal%20commitment%20to%20return%20any%20potential%20benefits%20emanating%20from%20such%20sharing%20to%20the%20South%2C%20says%20a%20Geneva-based%20health%20analyst.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPathogen%20samples%20or%20their%20genetic%20sequencing%20data%20are%20important%20to%20develop%20vaccines%2C%20diagnostics%20or%20medicines%20against%20infections%20from%20these%20pathogens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20developed%20countries%20want%20to%20access%20pathogens%20or%20their%20genetic%20sequence%20data%20to%20develop%20the%20above-mentioned%20medical%20products%20but%20are%20not%20ready%20to%20share%20the%20technology%20or%20know-how%20related%20to%20those%20products.%20Often%20such%20medical%20products%20are%20protected%20through%20patents%20and%20trade%20secrets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20the%20One%20Health%20agenda%20serves%20the%20purposes%20of%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industries%20of%20the%20developed%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202022%2C%20four%20international%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fresources%2Fpublication%2Fone-health-joint-plan-action-2022-2026%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eorganisations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20viz.%20The%20Food%20and%20Agriculture%20Organisation%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20(FAO)%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20Environment%20Programme%20(UNEP)%2C%20the%20(WHO)%2C%20and%20the%20World%20Organisation%20for%20Animal%20Health%20(WOAH%2C%20formerly%2C%20the%20Office%20International%20des%20Epizooties)%2C%20adopted%20the%20One%20Health%20Joint%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(2022-26).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20G-20%20Health%20Ministerial%20Declaration%20contains%20language%20to%20endorse%20this%20joint%20action%20plan.%20This%20joint%20action%20plan%20requires%20a%20range%20of%20norms%20and%20standard%20settings%20and%20information%20sharing%20without%20clearly%20mentioning%20the%20governance%20of%20this%20shared%20information%20and%20the%20benefit%20emanating%20from%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20trade%20experts%20in%20Geneva%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20One%20Health%20agenda%20that%20is%20being%20pushed%20because%20information%20on%20plants%20and%20animal%20pathogens%20could%20be%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20prevent%20agricultural%20imports%20from%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20by%20raising%20the%20requirements%20to%20prove%20the%20absence%20of%20such%20pathogens%20in%20agriculture%20and%20meat%20products.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20joint%20action%20plan%20mentions%20access%20to%20quality%20vaccines%2C%20there%20are%20no%20details%20in%20the%20plan%20on%20how%20to%20achieve%20that%20target.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20joint%20action%20plan%20was%20developed%20without%20any%20effective%20participation%20from%20countries%20except%20through%20an%20online%20consultation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20endorsement%20of%20the%20joint%20action%20plan%20is%20akin%20to%20giving%20a%20seal%20of%20approval%20to%20the%20plan%2C%20which%20many%20G20%20developing%20country%20members%20have%20no%20informed%20understanding%20of%20and%20neither%20did%20they%20participate%20in%20its%20development.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20many%20developed%20countries%20inserted%20the%20One%20Health%20agenda%20in%20the%20ongoing%20negotiations%20on%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20Political%20Declaration%20on%20Pandemic%20Prevention%2C%20Preparedness%20and%20Response%20(PPPR).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20inclusion%20of%20AMR%20into%20health%20emergency%20surveillance%20is%20an%20overlapping%20item%20under%20the%20One%20Health%20agenda.%20However%2C%20the%20most%20important%20implication%20is%20the%20extension%20of%20surveillance%20on%20AMR-related%20areas%20and%20thus%20converting%20health%20emergency%20surveillance%20into%20AMR%20surveillance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20EU%20has%20already%20presented%20extensive%20proposals%20for%20inclusion%20as%20part%20of%20the%20new%20pandemic%20instrument%20currently%20under%20negotiations%20at%20WHO.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20it%20is%20an%20EU%20agenda.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAccess%20to%20medical%20countermeasures%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20this%20agenda%20item%2C%20India%20is%20pushing%20other%20G20%20developing%20country%20counterparts%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20platform%20on%20medical%20countermeasures%20to%20facilitate%20access%20to%20vaccines%2C%20therapeutics%20(medicines)%20and%20diagnostics.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20a%20new%20idea%20but%20is%20an%20institutionalisation%20of%20a%20failed%20experiment%20known%20as%20Access%20to%20COVID-19%20Tools%20Accelerator%20(ACT-A)%2C%20which%20was%20established%20in%20April%202020%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20based%20on%20a%20white%20paper%20developed%20by%20BMGF.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EACT-A%20was%20envisaged%20as%20a%20multi-stakeholder%20platform%20without%20any%20effective%20say%20for%20the%20WHO%20member%20states.%20The%20Strategic%20Review%20of%20ACT-A%20points%20out%20the%20member%20states%E2%80%99%20lack%20of%20participation%20as%20a%20serious%20shortcoming.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20the%20WHO%20had%20already%20envisaged%20a%20plan%20to%20give%20a%20new%20lease%20of%20life%20to%20ACT-A%20under%20a%20new%20name%20and%20mooted%20the%20idea%20of%20establishing%20a%20Platform%20for%20Medical%20Counter-Measures%20(MCM).%20The%20WHO%20delegation%20attended%20the%201st%20G20%20Health%20Working%20Group%20meeting%20in%20Trivandrum%20where%20it%20sold%20this%20idea%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20G20%20presidency%20apparently%20bought%20this%20idea%20without%20a%20second%20thought.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20Africa%20and%20Norway%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.za%2Fspeeches%2Fsouth-africa-and-norway-host-high-level-technical-meeting-medical-countermeasures-23-24-feb%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehosted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20joint-meeting%20in%20Johannesburg%20to%20discuss%20the%20new%20lease%20of%20life%20to%20ACT-A%20through%20the%20Platform%20for%20MCM.%20This%20was%20envisaged%20as%20a%20mechanism%20to%20carry%20out%20research%20and%20development%20(R%26amp%3BD)%20on%20vaccines%2C%20therapeutics%20and%20diagnostics%20and%20then%20licence%20these%20for%20production%20and%20supply%20in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20thus%20excluding%20many%20developing%20countries%20like%20Argentina%2C%20Brazil%20and%20even%20African%20countries%20like%20Namibia.%20This%20has%20created%20opposition%20among%20many%20developing%20countries%20including%20Brazil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20reason%20for%20opposition%20is%20that%20the%20Platform%20for%20MCM%20is%20envisaged%20as%20a%20multi-stakeholder%20mechanism%20including%20donors%20as%20part%20of%20its%20governance%2C%20thus%20accommodating%20BMGF.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20developing%20countries%2C%20especially%20African%20nations%2C%20view%20this%20WHO%20move%20as%20scuttling%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20mechanism%20for%20production%20and%20supply%20as%20part%20of%20the%20new%20pandemic%20instrument%20currently%20under%20negotiation.%20Many%20delegates%20in%20Geneva%20believe%20that%20the%20mechanism%20under%20the%20new%20pandemic%20instrument%20would%20create%20accountability%20and%20shared%20ownership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERealising%20the%20resistance%2C%20WHO%20is%20now%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20establishing%20only%20an%20interim%20platform%20and%20further%20progress%20is%20subject%20to%20the%20negotiations%20on%20the%20pandemic%20instrument.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20endorsement%20of%20such%20a%20platform%20has%20already%20come%20from%C2%A0%20industrialised%20countries%20grouped%20under%20the%20G7.%20Further%2C%20many%20developed%20countries%20proposed%20language%20for%20the%20endorsement.%20The%20G7%20Leaders%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F05%2F20%2Fg7-hiroshima-leaders-communique%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECommunique%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20Hiroshima%20Summit%20in%20May%202023%C2%A0states%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20announce%20the%20G7%20Hiroshima%20Vision%20for%20Equitable%20Access%20to%20MCMs%20and%20launch%20the%20MCM%20Delivery%20Partnership%20for%20equitable%20access%20(MCDP)%20to%20contribute%20to%20more%20equitable%20access%20to%20and%20delivery%20of%20MCMs%20based%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20equity%2C%20inclusivity%2C%20efficiency%2C%20affordability%2C%20quality%2C%20accountability%2C%20agility%20and%20speed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20developed%20countries%20are%20trying%20to%20obtain%20an%20endorsement%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20interim%20platform.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20week%20in%20New%20York%2C%20during%20the%20negotiations%20on%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20Political%20Declaration%20on%20PPPR%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Edeveloped%20countries%20made%20the%20following%20proposa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3El%3A%20%E2%80%9CUrge%20sustainable%2C%20affordable%2C%20fair%2C%20equitable%2C%20effective%2C%20efficient%20and%20timely%20access%20to%20medical%20countermeasures%2C%20including%20vaccines%2C%20therapeutics%2C%20diagnostics%20and%20other%20health%20products%20and%20call%20on%20the%20WHO%20to%20coordinate%20this%20with%20relevant%20partners%20to%20ensure%20its%20ability%20for%20interim%20mechanism%2C%20ensuring%20coherence%20with%20the%20mindful%20of%20the%2Fwithout%20prejudice%20of%20the%20ongoing%20discussions%20of%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Negotiating%20Body%20and%20the%20Working%20Group%20on%20Amendments%20to%20the%20International%20Health%20Regulations%20(2005)%20in%20Geneva.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20revealed%20that%20the%20G20%20draft%20Health%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Declaration%20also%20contains%20more%20or%20less%20the%20same%20text%2C%20thus%20giving%20an%20endorsement%20for%20the%20WHO%20to%20establish%20the%20interim%20platform%20on%20MCM.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EImplications%20on%20credibility%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20India%20is%20engaged%20in%20hectic%20diplomatic%20efforts%2C%20through%20its%20missions%20abroad%2C%20including%20the%20UN%20Mission%20in%20Geneva%2C%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%20G20%20Health%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Declaration.%20India%E2%80%99s%20apparent%20desperation%20to%20showcase%20the%20success%20of%20its%20G20%20presidency%20has%20also%20allegedly%20forced%20it%20to%20support%20the%20developed%20country%20agenda%20of%20One%20Health%20and%20Platform%20for%20MCM%20in%20WHO%20and%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20creates%20an%20image%20of%20being%20an%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Csatellite%20country%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20North%20and%20severely%20dents%20India%E2%80%99s%20credibility%20as%20an%20independent%20development%20arbitrator%20in%20various%20international%20forums.%20The%20immediate%20consequences%20of%20such%20erosion%20of%20credibility%20would%20be%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20build%20a%20coalition%20in%20forums%20like%20the%20WTO.%20The%20health%20agenda%20also%20once%20again%20proves%20that%20forums%20like%20the%20G20%20are%20being%20used%20by%20the%20G7%20to%20obtain%20endorsement%20and%20legitimacy%20for%20their%20agenda%20from%20developing%20countries%20like%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20vacuous%20Modi%20Administration%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20in%20finance%2C%20trade%2C%20and%20now%20health%2C%20India%20seems%20to%20have%20become%20a%20champion%20of%20that%20proverbial%20saying%3A%20Run%20with%20hares%20and%20hunt%20with%20hounds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fravi-kanth-devarakonda%5C%22%3ERavi%20Kanth%20Devarakonda%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691139400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04141303%2FFjHNMmeakAEkbxa.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22